{
  "stem": "33.3",
  "chunk_idx": 14,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "But on April the 14th, it was a Saturday, and we had no reading material or anything, but somehow somebody gave me a book-- a German novel-- I don't know-- I found it somewhere-- maybe the SS who left some stuff behind.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "I don't remember.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But I found the book.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And I was lying on the earth, basically, by the fence, on the other side of the camp.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "It was a nice spring day, and I was reading.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And there was no work in the factory the last week or so anymore.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And somebody came again and shouted, they're coming, they're coming.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "For the first five minutes, I think, I didn't get up.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "But then I was running to the gate like everybody else.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And our gates were open actually by French POWs.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "There was a POW camp on the other side of the town, and I guess they were liberated first, that side.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "And the French POWs, most of them Jewish guys, opened our gates.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And then, of course, the American army was coming.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "The POWs had a lot more communication with the outside world than we did.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And also there were the so-called free workers-- I mean, free, quote, unquote, 'free.' They were mainly.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "French I guess some Belgium and Dutch, too, who were forced to go work in Germany.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And they had a lot more freedom than we did.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "They were also in camps, but they had some freedom of movement.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "We were isolated.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "We had no news because we were in-- you know, locked in camps.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "But while we worked in the factory, there were some French workers-- they're mechanics who worked-- and I remember one of them, Josef, was a French mechanic.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
